-- Alstom to Furnish 68 Wind Turbines to Brazil’s Casa dos Ventos
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2012-09-14T14:14:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-14/alstom-to-furnish-68-wind-turbines-to-brazil-s-casa-dos-ventos.html
Alstom SA (ALO) , the world’s third-
largest power-equipment maker, has agreed to supply 68 wind
turbines to Brazilian developer Casa dos Ventos for projects in
the northeastern city of Joao Camara.  The power equipment, with more than 180 megawatts of
generation capacity, will be produced at its factory in Bahia
state, Levallois-Perret, France-based Alstom said today on its
website. The contract, worth 230 million euros ($302.3 million),
may be signed by the end of the month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jasmina Kelemen at 
 jkelemen2@bloomberg.net  